stateDiagram-v2
  [*] --> created: createHost({ runtime })

  created --> starting: host.start()
  starting --> ready: Runtime ready → services started (dependency order)
  starting --> failed: a service failed to start (ServiceLifecycleError)

  ready --> degraded: a service or the runtime became unhealthy
  degraded --> ready: health recovered

  ready --> shutting_down: host.stop()
  degraded --> shutting_down: host.stop()
  shutting_down --> stopped: services stopped (reverse) → Runtime stopped

  ready --> restarting: host.restart()
  degraded --> restarting: host.restart()
  restarting --> ready: stop services → runtime.restart() → start services
  restarting --> failed: a restart step failed

  failed --> [*]
  stopped --> [*]

  note right of starting
    Startup order: Runtime (delegated to ADR-043) THEN hosted
    services in deterministic dependency order (ADR-042 graph).
    Each service.start(ctx) receives ONLY its declared context slices.
  end note

  note right of shutting_down
    Shutdown order: hosted services in REVERSE dependency order
    (graceful — a failing stop is recorded, not fatal) THEN the
    Runtime (ADR-043 timeout/force policy applies).
  end note

  state "per-service states" as PS {
    [*] --> registered
    registered --> s_starting: start
    s_starting --> started
    started --> s_stopping: stop
    s_stopping --> s_stopped
    s_starting --> s_failed: start threw
  }
